28/******** IR Module ********/

30const PrimFuncNode* GetRootPrimFunc(const IRModule& mod, const StmtNode* root_block,
31 GlobalVar* result_g_var) {
32 for (const auto& kv : mod->functions) {
33 const GlobalVar& g_var = kv.first;
34 const BaseFunc& base_func = kv.second;
35 if (const auto* func = base_func.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
36 if (const auto* realize = func->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
37 if (realize->block.get() == root_block) {
38 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
39 *result_g_var = g_var;
40 }
41 return func;
42 }
43 }
44 }
45 }
46 LOG(FATAL) << "IndexError: Could not get the corresponding function in the schedule state of the "
47 "statement:\n"
48 << GetRef<Stmt>(root_block);
49 throw;
50}
51
52const PrimFuncNode* FindEntryFunc(const IRModule& mod, GlobalVar* result_g_var) {
53 GlobalVar result = NullValue<GlobalVar>();
54 // Priority 1: PrimFunc marked as `tir::attr::kIsEntryFunc`
55 int num_prim_func = 0;
56 const tir::PrimFuncNode* main_func = nullptr;
57 const tir::PrimFuncNode* last_func = nullptr;
58 for (const auto& kv : mod->functions) {
59 GlobalVar gv = kv.first;
60 BaseFunc base_func = kv.second;
61 if (const auto* func = base_func.as<tir::PrimFuncNode>()) {
62 last_func = func;
63 if (func->HasNonzeroAttr(tir::attr::kIsEntryFunc)) {
64 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
65 *result_g_var = gv;
66 }
67 return func;
68 }
69 if (gv->name_hint == "main") {
70 main_func = func;
71 result = gv;
72 }
73 ++num_prim_func;
74 }
75 }
76 // Priority 2: PrimFunc whose name is `main`
77 if (main_func != nullptr) {
78 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
79 *result_g_var = result;
80 }
81 return main_func;
82 }
83 // Priority 3: The only PrimFunc in the IRModule
84 if (num_prim_func == 1) {
85 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
86 *result_g_var = result;
87 }
88 return last_func;
89 }
90 return nullptr;
91}

93/******** Scope ********/

95StmtSRef GetScopeRoot(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& sref,
96 bool require_stage_pipeline) {
97 class RootBlockError : public ScheduleError {
98 public:
99 explicit RootBlockError(IRModule mod) : mod_(mod) {}
100 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
101 String FastErrorString() const final {
102 return "ScheduleError: The primitive does not operate on the root block";
103 }
104 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
105 return "The primitive does not operate on the root block";
106 }
107 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
108 IRModule mod_;
109 };
110
111 class NotStagePipelineError : public ScheduleError {
112 public:
113 explicit NotStagePipelineError(IRModule mod, Block block) : mod_(mod), block_(block) {}
114 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
115 String FastErrorString() const final {
116 return "ScheduleError: The scope root is not a stage pipeline";
117 }
118 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
119 return R"(The scope {0} is not a stage pipeline.
120Definition of a scope that is a stage pipeline:
121- The region cover property holds for every of its child blocks
122- No write-after-read dependency or opaque dependency,
123- only read-after-write and write-after-write are allowed
124- All the statements in the scope are schedulable statements, i.e. Block and For
125)";
126 }
127 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
128 IRModule mod_;
129 Block block_;
130 };
131
132 StmtSRef scope_root_sref{nullptr};
133 StmtSRef scope_root_subtree{nullptr};
134 // Step 1. Find the scope root and the subtree that the given sref is in
135 {
136 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref->parent;
137 const StmtSRefNode* subtree = sref.get();
138 for (; p != nullptr; subtree = p, p = p->parent) {
139 if (p->stmt->IsInstance<BlockNode>()) {
140 scope_root_sref = GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
141 scope_root_subtree = GetRef<StmtSRef>(subtree);
142 break;
143 }
144 }
145 if (p == nullptr) {
146 throw RootBlockError(self->mod);
147 }
148 }
149 // Step 2. Handle `require_stage_pipeline`
150 if (require_stage_pipeline) {
151 bool stage_pipeline = self->GetBlockInfo(scope_root_sref).scope->stage_pipeline;
152 if (stage_pipeline == false) {
153 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_root_sref);
154 throw NotStagePipelineError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block));
155 }
156 }
157 return scope_root_sref;
158}
159
160ScopeBlockLoopInfo GetScopeBlockLoopInfo(const Block& scope_block) {
161 struct Collector : public StmtVisitor {
162 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* realize) final {
163 result.realizes.push_back(GetRef<BlockRealize>(realize));
164 const Array<IterVar>& iter_vars = realize->block->iter_vars;
165 const Array<PrimExpr>& iter_values = realize->iter_values;
166 ICHECK_EQ(iter_vars.size(), iter_values.size());
167 int n = realize->iter_values.size();
168 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
169 const IterVar& iter_var = iter_vars[i];
170 const PrimExpr& iter_value = iter_values[i];
171 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* vars = nullptr;
172 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
173 vars = &result.spatial_vars;
174 } else {
175 vars = &result.non_spatial_vars;
176 }
177 PostOrderVisit(iter_value, [vars](const ObjectRef& obj) {
178 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
179 vars->insert(var);
180 }
181 });
182 }
183 }
184
185 ScopeBlockLoopInfo result;
186 } visitor;
187 visitor(scope_block->body);
188 return std::move(visitor.result);
189}

191/*!
192 * \brief Check whether the given sref_a is higher than or equal to sref_b.
193 */
194void CheckSRefHigherOrEqual(const StmtSRef& sref_a, const StmtSRef& sref_b) {
195 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref_b.get();
196 for (; p != nullptr; p = p->parent) {
197 if (p == sref_a.get()) {
198 return;
199 }
200 }
201 CHECK(false) << "Expect StmtSRef " << sref_a << "to be higher than or equal to " << sref_b;
202}

204/*!
205 * \brief Check the dominant property of a block:
206 * the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under the
207 * given root scope.
208 * \param self The schedule state.
209 * \param scope_root_sref The StmtSRef corresponding to the root scope.
210 * \param block_sref The block whose dominant property is to be checked.
211 * \return A boolean indicating if the block is a dominant block.
212 */
213bool IsDominantBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref,
214 const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
215 std::unordered_map<Buffer, Array<StmtSRef>, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> buffer_writers;
216 CheckSRefHigherOrEqual(scope_root_sref, block_sref);
217 const BlockNode* maybe_root_block = scope_root_sref->StmtAs<BlockNode>();
218 if (maybe_root_block) {
219 BlockScope scope = self->GetBlockScope(scope_root_sref);
220 buffer_writers = scope->buffer_writers;
221 } else {
222 // Collect all child blocks of root sub-tree, and merge their buffer writers.
223 Array<StmtSRef> child_block_srefs = GetChildBlockSRefOnSRefTree(self, scope_root_sref);
224 for (const StmtSRef& child_block_sref : child_block_srefs) {
225 BlockScope child_scope = self->GetBlockScope(child_block_sref);
226 for (const auto& it : child_scope->buffer_writers) {
227 buffer_writers.insert(it);
228 }
229 }
230 }
231 // Check whether the input block is the only writer of its outputs
232 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
233 for (const BufferRegion& write_region : block->writes) {
234 if (buffer_writers.count(write_region->buffer)) {
235 if (buffer_writers.at(write_region->buffer).size() != 1) {
236 return false;
237 }
238 }
239 }
240 return true;
241}

243/*!
244 * \brief A helper function that checks whether a given block is a complete block under the scope,
245 * or return the condition it violates if it is not a complete block
246 * \param self The schedule state
247 * \param block_sref The block to be checked
248 * \param scope_root_sref The sref to the root block of the scope that `block_sref` is in
249 * \return 0 if the block is a complete block, or a positive integer indicating which condition is
250 * first violated
251 */
252int CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
253 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
254 // Cond 1. All block vars are data parallel
255 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
256 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
257 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar) {
258 return 1;
259 }
260 }
261 // Cond 2. Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output,
262 // dominating the reader of its output buffers
263 if (!IsDominantBlock(self, scope_root_sref, block_sref)) {
264 return 2;
265 }
266 // Cond 3. No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes
267 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> written_buffers;
268 written_buffers.reserve(block->writes.size());
269 for (const BufferRegion& write : block->writes) {
270 written_buffers.insert(write->buffer.get());
271 }
272 for (const BufferRegion& read : block->reads) {
273 if (written_buffers.count(read->buffer.get())) {
274 return 3;
275 }
276 }
277 return 0;
278}
279
280static const char* kCompleteBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a complete block:
2811) All block vars are data parallel
2822) Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers
2833) No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes)";
284
285static const char* kReductionBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a reduction block:
2861) The block has the `init` statement
2872) All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions
2883) All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars
2894) Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers
2905) The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers)";
291
292static const char* kLocalCompleteBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a local complete block:
2931) All block vars are data parallel
2942) Local Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under a given subtree
2953) No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes)";
296
297static const char* kLocalReductionBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a reduction block:
2981) The block has the `init` statement
2992) All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions
3003) All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars
3014) Local Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under a given subtree
3025) The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers)";
303
304bool IsCompleteBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
305 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
306 return CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref) == 0;
307}

309void CheckCompleteBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
310 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
311 class IncompleteBlockError : public ScheduleError {
312 public:
313 explicit IncompleteBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block, int violated_cond)
314 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)), violated_cond_(violated_cond) {}
315 String FastErrorString() const final { return "ScheduleError: Incomplete block"; }
316 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
317 std::ostringstream os;
318 os << "The block {0} is not a complete block - it violates condition #" << violated_cond_;
319 os << ".\n" << kCompleteBlockDefinition;
320 return os.str();
321 }
322 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
323 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
324 IRModule mod_;
325 Block block_;
326 int violated_cond_;
327 };
328
329 int error_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
330 if (error_code != 0) {
331 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
332 throw IncompleteBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), error_code);
333 }
334}

336/*!
337 * \brief A helper function that checks whether a given block is a reduction block under the scope,
338 * or return the condition it violates if it is not a reduction block
339 * \param self The schedule state
340 * \param block_sref The block to be checked
341 * \param scope_root_sref The sref to the root block of the scope that `block_sref` is in
342 * \return 0 if the block is a reduction block, or a positive integer indicating which condition is
343 * first violated
344 */
345int CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
346 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
347 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
348 // Cond 1. The block has the `init` statement.
349 if (!block->init.defined()) {
350 return 1;
351 }
352 // Cond 2. All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions.
353 if (!self->IsAffineBlockBinding(block_sref)) {
354 return 2;
355 }
356 // Cond 3. All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars. Meanwhile,
357 // we collect all the reduction block vars.
358 if (!ContainsOnlyDataParAndReductionBlockIter(block->iter_vars)) {
359 return 3;
360 }
361 // Cond 4. Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its
362 // output buffers.
363 if (!IsDominantBlock(self, scope_root_sref, block_sref)) {
364 return 4;
365 }
366 // Cond 5. The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers.
367 return ReductionIterNotIndexOutputBuffer(GetRef<Block>(block)) ? 0 : 5;
368}
369
370bool IsReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
371 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
372 return CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref) == 0;
373}
374
375void CheckReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
376 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
377 class NotReductionBlockError : public ScheduleError {
378 public:
379 explicit NotReductionBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block, int violated_cond)
380 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)), violated_cond_(violated_cond) {}
381 String FastErrorString() const final { return "ScheduleError: Not a reduction block"; }
382 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
383 std::ostringstream os;
384 os << "The block {0} is not a reduction block - it violates condition #" << violated_cond_;
385 os << ".\n" << kReductionBlockDefinition;
386 return os.str();
387 }
388 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
389 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
390 IRModule mod_;
391 Block block_;
392 int violated_cond_;
393 };
394
395 int error_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
396 if (error_code != 0) {
397 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
398 throw NotReductionBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), error_code);
399 }
400}

402void CheckCompleteOrReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
403 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
404 class NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError : public ScheduleError {
405 public:
406 explicit NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block,
407 int complete_block_error_code,
408 int reduction_block_error_code)
409 : mod_(mod),
410 block_(block),
411 complete_block_error_code_(complete_block_error_code),
412 reduction_block_error_code_(reduction_block_error_code) {}
413
414 String FastErrorString() const final {
415 return "ScheduleError: Not a complete or reduction block";
416 }
417 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
418 std::ostringstream os;
419 os << "The block {0} is not a complete block - it violates condition #"
420 << complete_block_error_code_;
421 os << ".\n" << kCompleteBlockDefinition;
422 os << "\nThe block is not a reduction block either - it violates condition #"
423 << reduction_block_error_code_;
424 os << ".\n" << kReductionBlockDefinition;
425 return os.str();
426 }
427 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
428 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
429
430 IRModule mod_;
431 Block block_;
432 int complete_block_error_code_;
433 int reduction_block_error_code_;
434 };
435
436 int complete_block_error_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
437 if (complete_block_error_code == 0) {
438 return;
439 }
440 int reduction_block_error_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
441 if (reduction_block_error_code == 0) {
442 return;
443 }
444 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
445 throw NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), complete_block_error_code,
446 reduction_block_error_code);
447}

449void CheckSubtreeCompactDataflow(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& subtree_root) {
450 class NotCompactDataFlowError : public ScheduleError {
451 public:
452 explicit NotCompactDataFlowError(IRModule mod, Stmt subtree_root, Block violate_block,
453 int local_complete_block_code, int local_reduction_block_code)
454 : mod_(std::move(mod)),
455 subtree_root_(std::move(subtree_root)),
456 violate_block_(std::move(violate_block)),
457 local_complete_block_code_(local_complete_block_code),
458 local_reduction_block_code_(local_reduction_block_code) {
459 ICHECK(subtree_root_->IsInstance<BlockNode>() || subtree_root_->IsInstance<ForNode>());
460 }
461 String FastErrorString() const final {
462 return "ScheduleError: The queried subtree root in SRef tree does not have compact dataflow, "
463 "because some of its child block on SRef tree is neither a local complete block nor a "
464 "local reduction block.";
465 }
466 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
467 std::ostringstream os;
468 os << "The queried subtree root {0} in SRef tree does not have compact dataflow, because "
469 "its child block {1} on SRef tree is neither a local complete block nor a local "
470 "reduction block.\n";
471 os << "It violates condition #" << local_complete_block_code_
472 << " as a local complete block.\n";
473 os << kLocalCompleteBlockDefinition << "\n";
474 os << "It violates condition #" << local_reduction_block_code_
475 << " as a local reduction block.\n";
476 os << kLocalReductionBlockDefinition << "\n";
477 return os.str();
478 }
479 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
480 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {subtree_root_, violate_block_}; }
481
482 IRModule mod_;
483 Stmt subtree_root_;
484 Block violate_block_;
485 int local_complete_block_code_;
486 int local_reduction_block_code_;
487 };
488
489 Array<StmtSRef> child_block_srefs = GetChildBlockSRefOnSRefTree(self, subtree_root);
490 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : child_block_srefs) {
491 int local_complete_block_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, subtree_root),
492 local_reduction_block_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, subtree_root);
493 if (local_complete_block_code != 0 && local_reduction_block_code != 0) {
494 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
495 throw NotCompactDataFlowError(self->mod, GetRef<Stmt>(subtree_root->stmt),
496 GetRef<Block>(block), local_complete_block_code,
497 local_reduction_block_code);
498 }
499 }
500}

502bool IsOutputBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
503 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
504 const BlockNode* scope_root = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_root_sref);
505 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
506 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> scope_allocated;
507 scope_allocated.reserve(scope_root->alloc_buffers.size());
508 for (const Buffer& buffer : scope_root->alloc_buffers) {
509 scope_allocated.insert(buffer.get());
510 }
511 for (const BufferRegion& buffer_region : block->writes) {
512 if (!scope_allocated.count(buffer_region->buffer.get())) {
513 return true;
514 }
515 }
516 return false;
517}

519void CheckNotOutputBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
520 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
521 class OutputBlockError : public ScheduleError {
522 public:
523 explicit OutputBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block) : mod_(mod), block_(block) {}
524 String FastErrorString() const final {
525 return "ScheduleError: Cannot operate on an output block";
526 }
527 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final { return "The block {0} is an output block"; }
528 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
529 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
530
531 IRModule mod_;
532 Block block_;
533 };
534 if (IsOutputBlock(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref)) {
535 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
536 throw OutputBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block));
537 }
538}

540std::vector<IterVarType> GetBlockVarTypes(const BlockNode* block) {
541 std::vector<IterVarType> results;
542 results.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
543 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
544 results.push_back(iter_var->iter_type);
545 }
546 return results;
547}
548
549std::vector<IterVarType> GetBlockVarTypes(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
550 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
551 return GetBlockVarTypes(block);
552}
553
554bool IsWriteCache(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
555 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
556 if (block->writes.size() != 1) {
557 return false;
558 }
559 const BufferRegion& write_region = block->writes[0];
560 for (const BufferRegion& read_region : block->reads) {
561 auto [exists, surjective, injective, ordered, no_const_read, no_shift_read] =
562 AnalyzeReadWritePattern(read_region, write_region);
563 // https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=81767
564 (void)exists;
565 (void)surjective;
566 (void)no_const_read;
567 (void)no_shift_read;
568 if (!(injective && ordered)) {
569 return false;
570 }
571 }
572 return true;
573}

575/******** Binding ********/
576
577bool IsAffineBinding(const BlockRealize& realize, const Map<Var, Range>& loop_var_ranges,
578 arith::Analyzer* analyzer) {
579 if (loop_var_ranges.empty()) {
580 return true;
581 }
582 auto res = arith::DetectIterMap(
583 /*indices=*/realize->iter_values,
584 /*input_iters=*/loop_var_ranges,
585 /*predicate=*/realize->predicate,
586 /*check_level=*/arith::IterMapLevel::Surjective,
587 /*analyzer=*/analyzer);
588 if (res->indices.empty()) {
589 return false;
590 }
591 for (const arith::IterSumExpr& sum_expr : res->indices) {
592 const Array<arith::IterSplitExpr>& args = sum_expr->args;
593 if (!args.empty() && !is_one(args[0]->scale)) {
594 return false;
595 }
596 }
597 return true;
598}
599
600void CheckPartialAffineBinding(const ScheduleState& self, Block block,
601 const Optional<StmtSRef>& high_exclusive) {
602 class NotAffineBindingError : public ScheduleError {
603 public:
604 explicit NotAffineBindingError(IRModule mod, Block block, Optional<StmtSRef> high_exclusive)
605 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)) {
606 if (high_exclusive.defined()) {
607 high_exclusive_loop_ = high_exclusive.value()->StmtAs<ForNode>();
608 }
609 }
610 String FastErrorString() const final {
611 std::ostringstream ss;
612 if (high_exclusive_loop_) {
613 ss << "ScheduleError: The block is required to have an partial affine binding under "
614 << high_exclusive_loop_->loop_var;
615 } else {
616 ss << "ScheduleError: The block is required to have an affine binding";
617 }
618 return ss.str();
619 }
620 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
621 std::ostringstream ss;
622 if (high_exclusive_loop_) {
623 ss << "The block {0} is required to have an partial affine binding under "
624 << high_exclusive_loop_->loop_var;
625 } else {
626 ss << "The block {0} is required to have an affine binding";
627 }
628 return ss.str();
629 }
630 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
631 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
632 IRModule mod_;
633 Block block_;
634 const ForNode* high_exclusive_loop_{nullptr};
635 };
636
637 StmtSRef block_sref = self->stmt2ref.at(block.get());
638 if (self->IsAffineBlockBinding(block_sref)) {
639 // check block cached state for global affineness
640 return;
641 }
642 if (block_sref->parent && high_exclusive.defined()) {
643 // if it is not of global affine binding, check affineness under high_exclusive,
644 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
645 Map<Var, Range> dom_map =
646 LoopDomainOfSRefTreePath(GetRef<StmtSRef>(block_sref->parent), high_exclusive);
647 if (IsAffineBinding(GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref), dom_map, &analyzer)) {
648 return;
649 }
650 }
651 throw NotAffineBindingError(self->mod, std::move(block), high_exclusive);
652}
653
654void CheckAffineBinding(const ScheduleState& self, Block block) {
655 CheckPartialAffineBinding(self, std::move(block), NullOpt);
656}
657
658Map<Var, Range> LoopDomainOfSRefTreePath(const StmtSRef& low_inclusive,
659 const Optional<StmtSRef>& high_exclusive,
660 const runtime::StorageScope& extra_relax_scope) {
661 Map<Var, Range> result;
662 const StmtSRefNode* p = low_inclusive.get();
663 const StmtSRefNode* limit = static_cast<const StmtSRefNode*>(high_exclusive.get());
664 for (; p != limit; p = p->parent) {
665 const ForNode* loop = p->StmtAs<ForNode>();
666 if (loop == nullptr) {
667 break;
668 }
669 result.Set(loop->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(loop->min, loop->extent));
670 }
671 if (extra_relax_scope.rank != runtime::StorageRank::kGlobal) {
672 for (; p; p = p->parent) {
673 if (const ForNode* loop = p->StmtAs<ForNode>()) {
674 if (loop->kind == ForKind::kThreadBinding) {
675 const String& thread_tag = loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag;
676 if (CanRelaxStorageUnderThread(extra_relax_scope,
677 runtime::ThreadScope::Create(thread_tag))) {
678 result.Set(loop->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(loop->min, loop->extent));
679 }
680 }
681 }
682 }
683 }
684 return result;
685}
686
687Map<Var, PrimExpr> GetBindings(const BlockRealize& realize) {
688 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
689 const Array<IterVar>& all_lhs = block->iter_vars;
690 const Array<PrimExpr>& all_rhs = realize->iter_values;
691 ICHECK_EQ(all_lhs.size(), all_rhs.size());
692 Map<Var, PrimExpr> result;
693 for (int i = 0, n = all_lhs.size(); i < n; ++i) {
694 const IterVar& lhs = all_lhs[i];
695 const PrimExpr& rhs = all_rhs[i];
696 result.Set(lhs->var, rhs);
697 }
698 return result;
699}

701bool GetVarsTouchedByBlockIters(const BlockRealize& block_realize,
702 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* data_par_vars,
703 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* reduce_vars) {
704 Block block = block_realize->block;
705 ICHECK(block_realize->block.same_as(block))
706 << "ValueError: The input `block_realize` is required to be the exact BlockRealize of the "
707 "input block";
708
709 bool has_block_vars_of_other_types = false;
710 ICHECK_EQ(block->iter_vars.size(), block_realize->iter_values.size());
711 int n = static_cast<int>(block->iter_vars.size());
712 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
713 const IterVar& iter_var = block->iter_vars[i];
714 const PrimExpr& iter_value = block_realize->iter_values[i];
715 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* set = nullptr;
716 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
717 set = data_par_vars;
718 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kCommReduce) {
719 set = reduce_vars;
720 } else {
721 has_block_vars_of_other_types = true;
722 }
723 if (set == nullptr) {
724 continue;
725 }
726 Array<Var> vars_in_binding = UndefinedVars(iter_value);
727 for (const Var& var : vars_in_binding) {
728 set->insert(var.get());
729 }
730 }
731
732 return has_block_vars_of_other_types;
733}

779 struct Collector : public StmtVisitor {
780 static Array<BlockRealize> Collect(const Stmt& stmt) {
781 Collector collector;
782 collector(stmt);
783 return std::move(collector.result_);
784 }
785
786 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* block_realize) final {
787 result_.push_back(GetRef<BlockRealize>(block_realize));
788 }
789
790 Array<BlockRealize> result_;
791 };
792
793 if (parent_sref->stmt->IsInstance<ForNode>()) {
794 const auto* loop = static_cast<const ForNode*>(parent_sref->stmt);
795 return Collector::Collect(loop->body);
796 } else if (parent_sref->stmt->IsInstance<BlockNode>()) {
797 const auto* block = static_cast<const BlockNode*>(parent_sref->stmt);
798 return Collector::Collect(block->body);
799 }
800 ICHECK(false) << "Unreachable";
801 throw;

840BlockRealize GetBlockRealize(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
841 struct BlockRealizeFinder : public StmtVisitor {
842 explicit BlockRealizeFinder(const BlockNode* target_block)
843 : target_block(target_block), result(nullptr) {}
844
845 void VisitStmt(const Stmt& stmt) final {
846 if (result != nullptr) {
847 return;
848 }
849 StmtVisitor::VisitStmt(stmt);
850 }
851
852 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* block_realize) final {
853 if (block_realize->block.get() == target_block) {
854 result = block_realize;
855 }
856 // No need to visit recursively, since the deeper BlockRealizes must not be the result.
857 }
858
859 const BlockNode* target_block;
860 const BlockRealizeNode* result;
861 };
862
863 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
864 if (block_sref->parent == nullptr) {
865 const PrimFuncNode* func = GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, block, nullptr);
866 return Downcast<BlockRealize>(func->body);
867 } else {
868 BlockRealizeFinder finder(block);
869 finder(GetRef<Stmt>(block_sref->parent->stmt));
870 ICHECK(finder.result != nullptr)
871 << "InternalError: Cannot find the BlockRealize of block " << GetRef<Block>(block);
872 return GetRef<BlockRealize>(finder.result);
873 }
874}
875
876IterVarType GetLoopIterType(const StmtSRef& loop_sref) {
877 const ForNode* loop = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loop_sref);
878 const Var& loop_var = loop->loop_var;
879 int n_spatial = 0;
880 int n_reduce = 0;
881 int n_other = 0;
882 auto f_visit = [&loop_var, &n_spatial, &n_reduce, &n_other](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
883 if (const auto* realize = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
884 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
885 // Number of block vars and their bindings
886 ICHECK_EQ(realize->iter_values.size(), block->iter_vars.size());
887 size_t n = realize->iter_values.size();
888 for (size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
889 const IterVar& iter_var = block->iter_vars[i];
890 const PrimExpr& binding = realize->iter_values[i];
891 // Categorize the current block var
892 int* ref = nullptr;
893 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
894 ref = &n_spatial;
895 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kCommReduce) {
896 ref = &n_reduce;
897 } else {
898 ref = &n_other;
899 }
900 // Visit the binding to see if `loop_var` appears
901 PostOrderVisit(binding, [&ref, &loop_var](const ObjectRef& obj) -> void {
902 if (obj.same_as(loop_var)) {
903 (*ref) += 1;
904 }
905 });
906 }
907 return false;
908 }
909 return true;
910 };
911 PreOrderVisit(loop->body, f_visit);
912 if (n_other) {
913 return IterVarType::kOpaque;
914 } else if (n_spatial && n_reduce) {
915 return IterVarType::kOpaque;
916 } else if (n_reduce) {
917 return IterVarType::kCommReduce;
918 } else {
919 return IterVarType::kDataPar;
920 }
921}
922
923StmtSRef GetSRefLowestCommonAncestor(const Array<StmtSRef>& srefs) {
924 CHECK(!srefs.empty()) << "ValueError: The input array is required to have at least one sref";
925
926 std::unordered_map<const StmtSRefNode*, size_t> sref_visited_cnt;
927 for (const StmtSRef& sref : srefs) {
928 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref.get();
929 while (p != nullptr) {
930 ++sref_visited_cnt[p];
931 p = p->parent;
932 }
933 }
934 size_t n_sref = srefs.size();
935 const StmtSRefNode* p = srefs[0].get();
936 while (p != nullptr && sref_visited_cnt[p] != n_sref) {
937 p = p->parent;
938 }
939 ICHECK(p != nullptr);
940 return GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
941}

947std::pair<Array<StmtSRef>, std::vector<int>> CollectComputeLocation(const ScheduleState& self,
948 const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
949 Array<StmtSRef> location_srefs;
950 std::vector<int> location_indices;
951
952 // Step 1. Add the "compute-root" candidate. Add the "compute-inline" candidate if the block can
953 // be inlined.
954 if (CanComputeInline(self, block_sref)) {
955 location_srefs.push_back(StmtSRef::InlineMark());
956 location_indices.push_back(-2);
957 }
958 location_srefs.push_back(StmtSRef::RootMark());
959 location_indices.push_back(-1);
960
961 // Step 2. If the block has no consumer, there is no more candidate.
962 Array<StmtSRef> consumers = GetConsumers(self, block_sref);
963 if (consumers.empty()) {
964 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
965 }
966
967 // Step 3. Get the deepest loop that the input block can be computed at (namely "boundary"). If
968 // such a loop cannot be found, there is no more candidate and we just return.
969 StmtSRef loop_boundary = consumers.size() > 1 ? GetSRefLowestCommonAncestor(consumers)
970 : GetRef<StmtSRef>(consumers[0]->parent);
971 if (loop_boundary->StmtAs<ForNode>() == nullptr) {
972 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
973 }
974
975 // Step 4. Collect the loops outside the first consumer and locate the boundary loop. The position
976 // of the boundary loop reveals the number of possible additional candidates.
977 Array<StmtSRef> loop_srefs = GetLoops(consumers[0]);
978 size_t lca_pos =
979 std::find(loop_srefs.begin(), loop_srefs.end(), loop_boundary) - loop_srefs.begin();
980 ICHECK_LT(lca_pos, loop_srefs.size());
981 size_t n_candidate = lca_pos + 1;
982
983 // Step 5. Find the position of the deepest data-parallel loop among the candidate loops. This
984 // position is used for removing the unwanted candidates from the perspective of performance.
985 std::vector<IterVarType> loop_iter_types;
986 loop_iter_types.reserve(n_candidate);
987 int i_last_datapar = -1;
988 for (size_t i = 0; i < n_candidate; ++i) {
989 // TODO(siyuan): improve the performance
990 IterVarType iter_type = GetLoopIterType(loop_srefs[i]);
991 loop_iter_types.push_back(iter_type);
992 if (iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
993 i_last_datapar = i;
994 }
995 }
996 // Step 6. Check and add the candidates in turn according to the following rules:
997 // - skip the unit loops (loops with extent 1);
998 // - do not consider the data-parallel loops after a not-data-parallel loop;
999 // - do not consider the trailing not-data-parallel loops.
1000 location_srefs.reserve(n_candidate + 2);
1001 location_indices.reserve(n_candidate + 2);
1002 bool visited_reduce = false;
1003 for (size_t i = 0; i < n_candidate; ++i) {
1004 const int64_t* loop_extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_srefs[i]);
1005 if (loop_extent != nullptr && *loop_extent == 1) {
1006 continue;
1007 }
1008
1009 if (loop_iter_types[i] == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1010 if (visited_reduce) {
1011 break;
1012 }
1013 } else {
1014 visited_reduce = true;
1015 if (static_cast<int>(i) > i_last_datapar) {
1016 break;
1017 }
1018 }
1019 if (CanComputeAt(self, block_sref, loop_srefs[i], true)) {
1020 location_srefs.push_back(loop_srefs[i]);
1021 location_indices.push_back(i);
1022 }
1023 }
1024
1025 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
1026}

1050ProducerConsumerSplit ProducerConsumerSplit::Find(
1051 const ScheduleState& self, const Array<Stmt>& subtrees,
1052 const Array<StmtSRef>& producer_block_srefs, const Array<StmtSRef>& consumer_block_srefs,
1053 std::unordered_map<const BlockNode*, const BlockRealizeNode*>* block2realize) {
1054 class InsertionPointNotFoundError : public ScheduleError {
1055 public:
1056 explicit InsertionPointNotFoundError(IRModule mod, int last_producer_position,
1057 int first_consumer_position)
1058 : mod_(mod),
1059 last_producer_position_(last_producer_position),
1060 first_consumer_position_(first_consumer_position) {}
1061
1062 String FastErrorString() const final {
1063 return "ScheduleError: Cannot find the insertion point that satisfies the producer-consumer "
1064 "constraint";
1065 }
1066
1067 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
1068 return "Cannot find the insertion point that satisfies the producer-consumer constraint. In "
1069 "0-based indexing, the last producer appears in subtree " +
1070 std::to_string(last_producer_position_) +
1071 ", and the first consumer appears in subtree " +
1072 std::to_string(first_consumer_position_);
1073 }
1074
1075 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1076
1077 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
1078
1079 private:
1080 IRModule mod_;
1081 int last_producer_position_;
1082 int first_consumer_position_;
1083 };
1084
1085 class Finder : public StmtVisitor {
1086 public:
1087 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* realize) final {
1088 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
1089 if (block2realize_) {
1090 block2realize_->emplace(block, realize);
1091 }
1092 if (producer_blocks_.count(block)) {
1093 ++this->n_producers_visited_;
1094 }
1095 if (consumer_blocks_.count(block)) {
1096 ++this->n_consumers_visited_;
1097 }
1098 }
1099
1100 std::unordered_map<const BlockNode*, const BlockRealizeNode*>* block2realize_;
1101 std::unordered_set<const StmtNode*> producer_blocks_;
1102 std::unordered_set<const StmtNode*> consumer_blocks_;
1103 int n_producers_visited_ = 0;
1104 int n_consumers_visited_ = 0;
1105 };
1106
1107 Finder finder;
1108 finder.block2realize_ = block2realize;
1109 // Set up the lookup table for producers
1110 finder.producer_blocks_.reserve(producer_block_srefs.size());
1111 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : producer_block_srefs) {
1112 finder.producer_blocks_.insert(block_sref->stmt);
1113 }
1114 // Set up the lookup table for consumers
1115 finder.consumer_blocks_.reserve(consumer_block_srefs.size());
1116 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : consumer_block_srefs) {
1117 finder.consumer_blocks_.insert(block_sref->stmt);
1118 }
1119 // Visit the subtrees
1120 int n = subtrees.size();
1121 int last_producer_position = -1;
1122 int first_consumer_position = n;
1123 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1124 int n_producers_visited_before = finder.n_producers_visited_;
1125 int n_consumers_visited_before = finder.n_consumers_visited_;
1126 finder(subtrees[i]);
1127 // Check if the subtree contains at least a producer
1128 if (finder.n_producers_visited_ != n_producers_visited_before) {
1129 last_producer_position = i;
1130 }
1131 // Check if the subtree contains at least a consumer
1132 if (finder.n_consumers_visited_ != n_consumers_visited_before) {
1133 if (first_consumer_position == n) {
1134 first_consumer_position = i;
1135 }
1136 }
1137 }
1138 if (last_producer_position >= first_consumer_position) {
1139 throw InsertionPointNotFoundError(self->mod, last_producer_position, first_consumer_position);
1140 }
1141 return ProducerConsumerSplit{last_producer_position, //
1142 first_consumer_position, //
1143 finder.n_producers_visited_, //
1144 finder.n_consumers_visited_};
1145}

1149BufferRegion GetNthAccessBufferRegion(const ScheduleState& self, const Block& block, int n,
1150 BufferIndexType index_type) {
1151 class BufferIndexOutOfRangeError : public ScheduleError {
1152 public:
1153 explicit BufferIndexOutOfRangeError(IRModule mod, Block block, int buffer_index,
1154 BufferIndexType index_type)
1155 : mod_(std::move(mod)),
1156 block_(std::move(block)),
1157 buffer_index_(buffer_index),
1158 index_type_(index_type) {}
1159
1160 String FastErrorString() const final {
1161 if (index_type_ == BufferIndexType::kWrite) {
1162 return "ScheduleError: The input `buffer_index` is out of range. It is required to be in "
1163 "range "
1164 "[0, num_write_regions) where `num_write_regions` is the number of buffer regions "
1165 "written by the block.";
1166 } else {
1167 return "ScheduleError: The input `buffer_index` is out of range. It is required to be in "
1168 "range "
1169 "[0, num_read_regions) where `num_read_regions` is the number of buffer regions "
1170 "read by the block.";
1171 }
1172 }
1173
1174 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
1175 std::ostringstream os;
1176 size_t num =
1177 index_type_ == BufferIndexType::kWrite ? block_->writes.size() : block_->reads.size();
1178 os << "The block {0} has " << num << " " << BufferIndexType2Str(index_type_)
1179 << " regions, so `buffer_index` is required to be in [0, " << num
1180 << "). However, the input `buffer_index` is " << buffer_index_
1181 << ", which is out of the expected range.";
1182 return os.str();
1183 }
1184
1185 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1186 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
1187
1188 private:
1189 IRModule mod_;
1190 Block block_;
1191 int buffer_index_;
1192 BufferIndexType index_type_;
1193 };
1194
1195 const Array<BufferRegion>& access_region =
1196 index_type == BufferIndexType::kWrite ? block->writes : block->reads;
1197
1198 if (n < 0 || static_cast<int>(access_region.size()) <= n) {
1199 throw BufferIndexOutOfRangeError(self->mod, block, n, index_type);
1200 }
1201 return access_region[n];
1202}

1208
1209std::pair<Optional<StmtSRef>, bool> GetBufferDefiningSite(const StmtSRef& block_sref,
1210 const Buffer& buffer) {
1211 // Climb up along the sref tree, and find the block where `buffer` is in alloc_buffers or
1212 // match_buffers.
1213 const StmtSRefNode* defining_site_sref = block_sref.get();
1214 while (defining_site_sref != nullptr) {
1215 const auto* block = defining_site_sref->StmtAs<BlockNode>();
1216 // If this sref is not a block sref, skip it.
1217 if (block == nullptr) {
1218 defining_site_sref = defining_site_sref->parent;
1219 continue;
1220 }
1221 // Try to find the buffer in `allloc_buffers`
1222 for (const Buffer& alloc_buffer : block->alloc_buffers) {
1223 if (buffer.same_as(alloc_buffer)) {
1224 return {GetRef<StmtSRef>(defining_site_sref), true};
1225 }
1226 }
1227 // We do not allow the buffer being defined in `match_buffer`.
1228 for (const MatchBufferRegion match_buffer : block->match_buffers) {
1229 if (buffer.same_as(match_buffer)) {
1230 return {GetRef<StmtSRef>(defining_site_sref), false};
1231 }
1232 }
1233 defining_site_sref = defining_site_sref->parent;
1234 }
1235 // If we cannot find the defining site block, it means that the buffer must be in the function's
1236 // buffer_map, which isn't an intermediate buffer.
1237 return {NullOpt, false};
1238}
1239
1240/******** Pattern Matcher ********/
1241
1242/*!
1243 * \brief PrimExpr pattern matcher.
1244 *
1245 * It is different from the pattern matcher in arith/pattern_match.h, which is dedicated
1246 * for compile-time constant patterns. This pattern matcher can work on dynamic user-specific
1247 * patterns.
1248 *
1249 * The code below shows how to use the pattern matcher.
1250 *
1251 * \code
1252 *
1253 * Var x("x"), y("y");
1254 * // use PrimExpr to declare patterns, x, y are holes that can be filled with
1255 * PatternMatcher pattern_matcher(x + y);
1256 * // expr = C[i, j] + A[i, k] * B[k, j], which is the expr we want to match
1257 * pattern_matcher.Match(expr);
1258 *
1259 * if (pattern_matcher.Success()) {
1260 * pattern_matcher.Eval(x) // C[i, j]
1261 * pattern_matcher.Eval(y) // A[i, k] * B[k, j]
1262 * }
1263 *
1264 * \endcode
1265 */
1266class PatternMatcher : public ExprVisitor {
1267 public:
1268 explicit PatternMatcher(PrimExpr pattern) : pattern_(std::move(pattern)) {}
1269
1270 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) final {
1271 auto it = filled_map_.find(op);
1272 if (it == filled_map_.end()) {
1273 filled_map_[op] = expr_to_match_;
1274 } else {
1275 ExprDeepEqual equal;
1276 if (it->second.same_as(expr_to_match_) || equal(it->second, expr_to_match_)) return;
1277 match_success_ = false;
1278 }
1279 }
1280
1281 void VisitExpr_(const LoadNode* op) final {
1282 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<LoadNode>();
1283 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1284 match_success_ = false;
1285 } else {
1286 if (!op->buffer_var.same_as(ptr->buffer_var)) {
1287 match_success_ = false;
1288 } else {
1289 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1290 expr_to_match_ = ptr->predicate;
1291 VisitExpr(op->predicate);
1292 expr_to_match_ = ptr->index;
1293 VisitExpr(op->index);
1294 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1295 }
1296 }
1297 }
1298
1299 void VisitExpr_(const LetNode* op) final {
1300 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<LetNode>();
1301 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1302 match_success_ = false;
1303 } else {
1304 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1305 expr_to_match_ = ptr->var;
1306 VisitExpr(op->var);
1307 expr_to_match_ = ptr->value;
1308 VisitExpr(op->value);
1309 expr_to_match_ = ptr->body;
1310 VisitExpr(op->body);
1311 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1312 }
1313 }
1314
1315 void VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) final {
1316 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<CallNode>();
1317 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1318 match_success_ = false;
1319 } else {
1320 if (!op->op.same_as(ptr->op)) {
1321 match_success_ = false;
1322 } else {
1323 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1324 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); ++i) {
1325 expr_to_match_ = ptr->args[i];
1326 VisitExpr(op->args[i]);
1327 }
1328 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1329 }
1330 }
1331 }
1332
1333#define TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(OpName) \
1334 void VisitExpr_(const OpName* op) { \
1335 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<OpName>(); \
1336 if (ptr == nullptr) { \
1337 match_success_ = false; \
1338 } else { \
1339 PrimExpr current = expr_to_match_; \
1340 expr_to_match_ = ptr->a; \
1341 VisitExpr(op->a); \
1342 expr_to_match_ = ptr->b; \
1343 VisitExpr(op->b); \
1344 std::swap(expr_to_match_, current); \
1345 } \
1346 }
1347
1348 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(AddNode);
1349 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(SubNode);
1350 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(MulNode);
1351 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(DivNode);
1352 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(ModNode);
1353 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(FloorDivNode);
1354 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(FloorModNode);
1355 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(MinNode);
1356 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(MaxNode);
1357 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(EQNode);
1358 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(NENode);
1359 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(LTNode);
1360 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(LENode);
1361 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(GTNode);

1363 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(AndNode);
1364 TVM_DECLARE_PATTERN_MATCHER_BIN_OP(OrNode);
1365
1366 void VisitExpr_(const CastNode* op) final {
1367 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<CastNode>();
1368 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1369 match_success_ = false;
1370 } else {
1371 if (!runtime::TypeEqual(op->dtype, ptr->dtype)) {
1372 match_success_ = false;
1373 } else {
1374 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1375 expr_to_match_ = ptr->value;
1376 VisitExpr(op->value);
1377 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1378 }
1379 }
1380 }
1381
1382 void VisitExpr_(const NotNode* op) final {
1383 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<NotNode>();
1384 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1385 match_success_ = false;
1386 } else {
1387 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1388 expr_to_match_ = ptr->a;
1389 VisitExpr(op->a);
1390 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1391 }
1392 }
1393
1394 void VisitExpr_(const SelectNode* op) final {
1395 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<SelectNode>();
1396 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1397 match_success_ = false;
1398 } else {
1399 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1400 expr_to_match_ = ptr->condition;
1401 VisitExpr(op->condition);
1402 expr_to_match_ = ptr->true_value;
1403 VisitExpr(op->true_value);
1404 expr_to_match_ = ptr->false_value;
1405 VisitExpr(op->false_value);
1406 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1407 }
1408 }
1409
1410 void VisitExpr_(const RampNode* op) final {
1411 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<RampNode>();
1412 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1413 match_success_ = false;
1414 } else {
1415 if (op->lanes != ptr->lanes) {
1416 match_success_ = false;
1417 } else {
1418 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1419 expr_to_match_ = ptr->base;
1420 VisitExpr(op->base);
1421 expr_to_match_ = ptr->stride;
1422 VisitExpr(op->stride);
1423 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1424 }
1425 }
1426 }
1427
1428 void VisitExpr_(const BroadcastNode* op) final {
1429 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<BroadcastNode>();
1430 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1431 match_success_ = false;
1432 } else {
1433 if (op->lanes != ptr->lanes) {
1434 match_success_ = false;
1435 } else {
1436 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1437 expr_to_match_ = ptr->value;
1438 VisitExpr(op->value);
1439 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1440 }
1441 }
1442 }
1443
1444 void VisitExpr_(const ShuffleNode* op) final {
1445 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<ShuffleNode>();
1446 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1447 match_success_ = false;
1448 } else {
1449 if (op->vectors.size() != ptr->vectors.size() || op->indices.size() != ptr->indices.size()) {
1450 match_success_ = false;
1451 } else {
1452 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1453 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->indices.size(); ++i) {
1454 expr_to_match_ = ptr->indices[i];
1455 VisitExpr(op->indices[i]);
1456 }
1457 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->vectors.size(); ++i) {
1458 expr_to_match_ = ptr->vectors[i];
1459 VisitExpr(op->vectors[i]);
1460 }
1461 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1462 }
1463 }
1464 }
1465
1466 void VisitExpr_(const IntImmNode* op) final {
1467 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<IntImmNode>();
1468 match_success_ = ptr != nullptr && op->value == ptr->value;
1469 }
1470
1471 void VisitExpr_(const FloatImmNode* op) final {
1472 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<FloatImmNode>();
1473 match_success_ = ptr != nullptr && op->value == ptr->value;
1474 }
1475
1476 void VisitExpr_(const StringImmNode* op) final {
1477 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<StringImmNode>();
1478 match_success_ = ptr != nullptr && op->value == ptr->value;
1479 }
1480
1481 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
1482 const auto* ptr = expr_to_match_.as<BufferLoadNode>();
1483 if (ptr == nullptr) {
1484 match_success_ = false;
1485 } else {
1486 if (!op->buffer.same_as(ptr->buffer) || op->indices.size() != ptr->indices.size()) {
1487 match_success_ = false;
1488 } else {
1489 PrimExpr tmp = expr_to_match_;
1490 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->indices.size(); ++i) {
1491 expr_to_match_ = ptr->indices[i];
1492 VisitExpr(op->indices[i]);
1493 }
1494 std::swap(expr_to_match_, tmp);
1495 }
1496 }
1497 }
1498
1499 void Match(const PrimExpr& expr_to_match) {
1500 this->match_success_ = true;
1501 this->filled_map_.clear();
1502 this->expr_to_match_ = expr_to_match;
1503 this->operator()(pattern_);
1504 }
1505
1506 PrimExpr Eval(const Var& var) {
1507 auto it = filled_map_.find(var.operator->());
1508 ICHECK(it != filled_map_.end()) << "Unknown pattern variable";
1509 ICHECK(match_success_) << "Match failed";
1510 return it->second;
1511 }
1512
1513 bool Success() const { return match_success_; }
1514
1515 private:
1516 bool match_success_{true};
1517 PrimExpr pattern_, expr_to_match_;
1518 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, PrimExpr> filled_map_;
1519};

1588std::pair<BufferStore, BufferStore> GetBufferStoresFromReductionBlock(
1589 const Optional<ScheduleState>& self, const Block& block) {
1590 static constexpr const char* error_str1 =
1591 "ValueError: The `init` and `body` of the reduction block are required to be both "
1592 "BufferStore so that rfactor or cross-thread reduction can be applied. However, a reduction "
1593 "block that doesn't meet this requirement is ";
1594 static constexpr const char* error_str2 =
1595 "ValueError: The `init` and `body` of the reduction block are required to have the same "
1596 "buffer access pattern so that rfactor or cross-thread reduction can be applied. However, a "
1597 "reduction block that doesn't meet this requirement is ";
1598
1599 const auto* init = block->init.as<BufferStoreNode>();
1600 const auto* body = block->body.as<BufferStoreNode>();
1601 if (!(init && body)) {
1602 if (self.defined()) {
1603 throw InitBodyNotBufferStoreError(self.value()->mod, block, init != nullptr, body != nullptr);
1604 } else {
1605 LOG(FATAL) << error_str1 << block;
1606 }
1607 }
1608 if (!init->buffer.same_as(body->buffer)) {
1609 if (self.defined()) {
1610 throw InitBodyNotSameBufferAccessError(self.value()->mod, block);
1611 } else {
1612 LOG(FATAL) << error_str2 << block;
1613 }
1614 }
1615 int ndim = static_cast<int>(init->buffer->shape.size());
1616 for (int i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
1617 if (!ExprDeepEqual()(init->indices[i], body->indices[i])) {
1618 if (self.defined()) {
1619 throw InitBodyNotSameBufferAccessError(self.value()->mod, block);
1620 } else {
1621 LOG(FATAL) << error_str2 << block;
1622 }
1623 }
1624 }
1625 return std::make_pair(GetRef<BufferStore>(init), GetRef<BufferStore>(body));
1626}

1636
1637bool ReductionIterNotIndexOutputBuffer(const Block& block) {
1638 // Step 1. Collect the reduction block iters.
1639 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> reduction_block_iters;
1640 reduction_block_iters.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
1641 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1642 if (iter_var->iter_type == kCommReduce) {
1643 reduction_block_iters.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1644 }
1645 }
1646 // Step 2. Check if the reduction block iters are used to index the output buffer.
1647 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffer_written;
1648 buffer_written.reserve(block->writes.size());
1649 for (const BufferRegion& write_region : block->writes) {
1650 buffer_written.insert(write_region->buffer.get());
1651 }
1652 auto f_uses_reduction_block_var = [&](const PrimExpr& expr) -> bool {
1653 return UsesVar(expr, [&](const VarNode* var) { //
1654 return reduction_block_iters.count(var);
1655 });
1656 };
1657 bool affected = false;
1658 PreOrderVisit(block->body, [&](const ObjectRef& obj) {
1659 if (affected) {
1660 return false;
1661 }
1662 const auto* store = obj.as<BufferStoreNode>();
1663 if (!store) {
1664 return true;
1665 }
1666 ICHECK(buffer_written.count(store->buffer.get()))
1667 << "ValueError: The buffer \"" << store->buffer
1668 << "\" is written in the block but is not in the block's signature";
1669 for (const PrimExpr& index : store->indices) {
1670 if (f_uses_reduction_block_var(index)) {
1671 affected = true;
1672 return false;
1673 }
1674 }
1675 return false;
1676 });
1677 return !affected;
1678}

1706std::tuple<CommReducer, PrimExpr, PrimExpr> GetReducerAndCombinerLhsRhs(
1707 const Optional<ScheduleState>& self, const PrimExpr& identity, const BufferStore& combiner) {
1708 CommReducer reducer{nullptr};
1709 PrimExpr combiner_lhs{nullptr}, combiner_rhs{nullptr};
1710 bool matched = FromIdentityCombiner(identity, combiner, &reducer, &combiner_lhs, &combiner_rhs);
1711 if (!matched) {
1712 if (self.defined()) {
1713 throw NoMatchedReducerError(self.value()->mod, identity, combiner);
1714 } else {
1715 LOG(FATAL) << "ValueError: No matched reducer for the identity and the combiner of the "
1716 "reduction block. So rfactor and cross-thread reduction cannot be applied.";
1717 }
1718 }
1719 return std::make_tuple(std::move(reducer), std::move(combiner_lhs), std::move(combiner_rhs));
1720}

1722/******** Commutative Reducer ********/
1723
1724bool MatchReducer(const CommReducer& reducer, const PrimExpr& identity, const PrimExpr& combiner,
1725 const BufferLoad& load, PrimExpr* lhs, PrimExpr* rhs) {
1726 if (!ExprDeepEqual()(reducer->identity_element[0], identity)) {
1727 return false;
1728 }
1729 PatternMatcher pattern_matcher(reducer->result[0]);
1730 pattern_matcher.Match(combiner);
1731 if (pattern_matcher.Success()) {
1732 PrimExpr lhs_tmp = pattern_matcher.Eval(reducer->lhs[0]);
1733 PrimExpr rhs_tmp = pattern_matcher.Eval(reducer->rhs[0]);
1734 if (ExprDeepEqual()(load, lhs_tmp)) {
1735 *lhs = std::move(lhs_tmp);
1736 *rhs = std::move(rhs_tmp);
1737 }
1738 return true;
1739 }
1740 return false;
1741}
1742
1743bool FromIdentityCombiner(const PrimExpr& identity, const BufferStore& combiner,
1744 CommReducer* result_reducer, PrimExpr* lhs, PrimExpr* rhs) {
1745 BufferLoad load(combiner->buffer, combiner->indices);
1746 // Check reduction patterns.
1747 for (const TypedPackedFunc<CommReducer(DataType)>& reducer_getter : GetReducerGetters()) {
1748 CommReducer reducer = reducer_getter(identity.dtype());
1749 if (MatchReducer(reducer, identity, combiner->value, load, lhs, rhs)) {
1750 *result_reducer = std::move(reducer);
1751 return true;
1752 }
1753 }
1754 return false;
1755}

1767
1768bool HasOp(const Stmt& stmt, const Array<Op>& ops) {
1769 std::unordered_set<const Object*> op_set;
1770 op_set.reserve(ops.size());
1771 for (const Op& op : ops) {
1772 op_set.insert(op.operator->());
1773 }
1774 bool found = false;
1775 PreOrderVisit(stmt, [&found, &op_set](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1776 if (found) {
1777 return false;
1778 }
1779 if (const auto* call = obj.as<CallNode>()) {
1780 if (op_set.count(call->op.operator->())) {
1781 found = true;
1782 }
1783 }
1784 return !found;
1785 });
1786 return found;
1787}
1788
1789bool HasIfThenElse(const Stmt& stmt) {
1790 bool has_branch = false;
1791 auto f_visit = [&has_branch](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1792 if (has_branch) {
1793 // stop visiting
1794 return false;
1795 }
1796 if (const auto* realize = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
1797 // Case 1: BlockRealize
1798 if (!is_one(realize->predicate)) {
1799 has_branch = true;
1800 }
1801 } else if (obj->IsInstance<IfThenElseNode>() || obj->IsInstance<SelectNode>()) {
1802 // Case 2: IfThenElse / Select
1803 has_branch = true;
1804 } else if (const auto* call = obj.as<CallNode>()) {
1805 // Case 3: Call the `if_then_else` operator
1806 static const Op& op_if_then_else = Op::Get("tir.if_then_else");
1807 if (call->op.same_as(op_if_then_else)) {
1808 has_branch = true;
1809 }
1810 }
1811 return !has_branch;
1812 };
1813 PreOrderVisit(stmt, f_visit);
1814 return has_branch;
1815}
1816
1817std::tuple</*exists=*/bool,
1818 /*surjective=*/bool,
1819 /*injective=*/bool,
1820 /*ordered=*/bool,
1821 /*no_const_read=*/bool,
1822 /*no_shift_read=*/bool>
1823AnalyzeReadWritePattern(const BufferRegion& read_region, const BufferRegion& write_region) {
1824 static constexpr const std::tuple<bool, bool, bool, bool, bool, bool> kNotExist =
1825 std::make_tuple(false, false, false, false, false, false);
1826 // Step 1. Extract the write indices
1827 int w_dim = write_region->buffer->shape.size();
1828 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, int> var2idx;
1829 var2idx.reserve(w_dim);
1830 for (int i = 0; i < w_dim; ++i) {
1831 const Range& dom = write_region->region[i];
1832 if (as_const_int(dom->extent) == nullptr) {
1833 return kNotExist;
1834 }
1835 if (const auto* v = dom->min.as<VarNode>()) {
1836 var2idx.emplace(v, i);
1837 } else {
1838 return kNotExist;
1839 }
1840 }
1841 // Step 2. Map each read index to a write index
1842 bool no_const_read = true;
1843 bool no_shift_read = true;
1844 int r_dim = read_region->buffer->shape.size();
1845 std::vector<int> mapped(r_dim, -1);
1846 for (int i = 0; i < r_dim; ++i) {
1847 const Range& dom = read_region->region[i];
1848 if (as_const_int(dom->extent) == nullptr) {
1849 return kNotExist;
1850 }
1851 // Case 1. Read index is a constant
1852 if (as_const_int(dom->min) != nullptr) {
1853 no_const_read = false;
1854 continue;
1855 }
1856 // Case 2. Read index cannot be recognized as `var +/- const`
1857 // where `var` is a write index and `const` is an optional constant shift
1858 Optional<IntImm> opt_const = NullOpt;
1859 const VarNode* var =
1860 static_cast<const VarNode*>(AnalyzeVarWithShift(dom->min, &opt_const).get());
1861 if (var == nullptr || !var2idx.count(var)) {
1862 return kNotExist;
1863 }
1864 // Case 3. Read index is `var +/- const`
1865 mapped[i] = var2idx.at(var);
1866 if (opt_const.defined()) {
1867 no_shift_read = false;
1868 }
1869 }
1870 // Step 3. Check if the mapping is ordered, and count how many times each var is mapped
1871 std::vector<int> mapped_counter(w_dim, 0);
1872 bool ordered = true;
1873 int last_mapped = -1;
1874 for (int i : mapped) {
1875 if (i != -1) {
1876 ++mapped_counter[i];
1877 if (last_mapped != -1 && last_mapped > i) {
1878 ordered = false;
1879 }
1880 last_mapped = i;
1881 }
1882 }
1883 // Step 4. Check if the mapping is surjective or injective
1884 // Surjective: each write index is mapped at least once
1885 // Injective: each write index is mapped at most once
1886 bool surjective = true;
1887 bool injective = true;
1888 for (int cnt : mapped_counter) {
1889 if (cnt == 0) {
1890 surjective = false;
1891 } else if (cnt >= 2) {
1892 injective = false;
1893 }
1894 }
1895 return std::make_tuple(/*exist=*/true, surjective, injective, ordered, no_const_read,
1896 no_shift_read);
1897}

1930bool IsSpatial(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1931 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1932 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1933 if (iter_var->iter_type != IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1934 return false;
1935 }
1936 }
1937 return true;

1940bool IsTrivialBinding(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1941 TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1942 Array<StmtSRef> loops = GetLoops(block_sref);
1943 Array<PrimExpr> binds = GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref)->iter_values;
1944 if (loops.size() != binds.size()) {
1945 return false;
1946 }
1947 for (int i = 0, n = loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1948 const ForNode* loop = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i]);
1949 if (binds[i].get() != loop->loop_var.get()) {
1950 return false;
1951 }
1952 }
1953 return true;
1954}

1956bool NeedsMultiLevelTiling(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1957 if (HasBeenMultiLevelTiled(block_sref)) {
1958 return false;
1959 }
1960 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1961 if (block->writes.size() != 1 || block->reads.empty() || IsSpatial(block_sref) ||
1962 !IsTrivialBinding(self, block_sref)) {
1963 return false;
1964 }
1965 const BufferNode* write_buffer = block->writes[0]->buffer.get();
1966 // Step 1. Sort out spatial block variables. Skip the block iters of domain [0, 1), since such
1967 // block iters distracts the following check of the unused block iters.
1968 std::vector<const VarNode*> spatial_block_vars;
1969 spatial_block_vars.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
1970 for (const IterVar& block_var : block->iter_vars) {
1971 const int64_t* dom_min = as_const_int(block_var->dom->min);
1972 const int64_t* dom_extent = as_const_int(block_var->dom->extent);
1973 bool has_trivial_dom =
1974 dom_min != nullptr && dom_extent != nullptr && *dom_min == 0 && *dom_extent == 1;
1975 if (block_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar && !has_trivial_dom) {
1976 spatial_block_vars.push_back(block_var->var.get());
1977 }
1978 }
1979 // Step 2. Enumerate each read region, check the number of block vars that are not used
1980 // to index the read region
1981 int total_unused_block_vars = 0;
1982 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> read_buffers;
1983 read_buffers.reserve(block->reads.size());
1984 for (const BufferRegion& buffer_region : block->reads) {
1985 const BufferNode* buffer = buffer_region->buffer.get();
1986 const Array<Range>& regions = buffer_region->region;
1987 // Step 2.1. Duplication of read buffers are not allowed
1988 if (read_buffers.insert(buffer).second == false) {
1989 return false;
1990 }
1991 // Step 2.2. Skip the reduction buffer
1992 if (buffer == write_buffer) {
1993 continue;
1994 }
1995 // Step 2.3. Collect the block vars that are used to index the read region
1996 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> vars;
1997 for (const Range& range : regions) {
1998 if (as_const_int(range->extent) == nullptr) {
1999 return false;
2000 }
2001 for (const Var& var : UndefinedVars(range->min)) {
2002 vars.insert(var.get());
2003 }
2004 }
2005 // Step 2.4. Check if the block vars are not used to index the read region
2006 int n_unused_block_vars = 0;
2007 for (const VarNode* block_var : spatial_block_vars) {
2008 if (vars.count(block_var) == 0) {
2009 ++n_unused_block_vars;
2010 }
2011 }
2012 total_unused_block_vars += n_unused_block_vars;
2013 }
2014 return total_unused_block_vars >= 1;
2015}

2017bool IsSpatialPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& func) {
2018 bool result = true;
2019 PreOrderVisit(func->body, [&result](const ObjectRef& obj) {
2020 if (result == false) {
2021 return false;
2022 }
2023 if (const auto* block = obj.as<BlockNode>()) {
2024 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
2025 if (iter_var->iter_type != IterVarType::kDataPar) {
2026 result = false;
2027 return false;
2028 }
2029 }
2030 }
2031 return true;
2032 });
2033 return result;
2034}

2036std::pair<int64_t, int64_t> GetCumulativeSpaceAndReductionLength(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
2037 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref) {
2038 Array<tir::StmtSRef> loops = tir::GetLoops(block_sref);
2039 int64_t cum_space_len = 1, cum_reduce_len = 1;
2040 /*
2041 * Return (-1, -1) if
2042 * 1. there is some loop with type other than kDataPar and kCommReduce;
2043 * 2. there is some loop which is dynamic.
2044 */
2045 for (const tir::StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
2046 tir::IterVarType type = GetLoopIterType(loop_sref);
2047 if (type == tir::kDataPar) {
2048 const int64_t* extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_sref);
2049 if (*extent != -1) {
2050 cum_space_len *= *extent;
2051 } else {
2052 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
2053 }
2054 } else if (type == tir::kCommReduce) {
2055 const int64_t* extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_sref);
2056 if (*extent != -1) {
2057 cum_reduce_len *= *extent;
2058 } else {
2059 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
2060 }
2061 } else {
2062 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
2063 }
2064 }
2065 return std::make_pair(cum_space_len, cum_reduce_len);
2066}
2067
2068bool NeedsRFactorOrCrossThreadReduction(const tir::ScheduleState& self, //
2069 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref, //
2070 int64_t max_parallel_extent, //
2071 int64_t max_parallel_basic) {
2072 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
2073 Array<tir::StmtSRef> loops = tir::GetLoops(block_sref);
2074
2075 // Cond 1. The block has only one write buffer
2076 if (block->writes.size() != 1) {
2077 return false;
2078 }
2079
2080 // Cond 2. The block is a reduction block and has trivial binding.
2081 const StmtSRef& scope_sref = GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref,
2082 /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
2083 if (!IsReductionBlock(self, block_sref, scope_sref) //
2084 || !IsTrivialBinding(self, block_sref) //
2085 || HasBeenMultiLevelTiled(block_sref)) {
2086 return false;
2087 }
2088
2089 // Cond 3. Every the loop axis must be either spatial axis or reduction axis.
2090 for (const tir::StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
2091 const tir::IterVarType& type = GetLoopIterType(loop_sref);
2092 if (type != tir::kDataPar && type != tir::kCommReduce) {
2093 return false;
2094 }
2095 }
2096
2097 // Cond 4. Whether there is at least one reduction loop.
2098 // Cond 5. The loops are continuous, and the body of the innermost loop is exactly the block.
2099 bool has_reduction_loop = false;
2100 for (size_t i = 0; i < loops.size(); ++i) {
2101 // Cond 4.
2102 if (GetLoopIterType(loops[i]) == tir::kCommReduce) {
2103 has_reduction_loop = true;
2104 }
2105
2106 // Cond 5.
2107 const ForNode* loop_i = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i]);
2108 if (i < loops.size() - 1) {
2109 const ForNode* loop_i1 = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i + 1]);
2110 if (loop_i->body.get() != loop_i1) {
2111 return false;
2112 }
2113 } else {
2114 const auto* block_realize = loop_i->body.as<tir::BlockRealizeNode>();
2115 if (!block_realize || block_realize->block.get() != block) {
2116 return false;
2117 }
2118 }
2119 }
2120 if (!has_reduction_loop) {
2121 return false;
2122 }
2123
2124 // Cond 6. Can successfully calculating the cumulative loop length.
2125 auto [cum_space_len, cum_reduce_len] = GetCumulativeSpaceAndReductionLength(self, block_sref);
2126 if (cum_space_len == -1 || cum_reduce_len == -1) {
2127 return false;
2128 }
2129
2130 // Cond 7.
2131 if (NeedsMultiLevelTiling(self, block_sref)) {
2132 // Do not use rfactor/cross-thread-reduction if we have enough parallelism on spatial loops.
2133 return !(cum_space_len >= cum_reduce_len || cum_space_len > max_parallel_extent);
2134 } else if (cum_reduce_len > 1) {
2135 // Always try rfactor/cross-thread-reduction for other reduction blocks.
2136 return cum_reduce_len > max_parallel_basic;
2137 } else {
2138 return false;
2139 }
2140}

2144/*! \brief Auxiliary data structure of information extracted from tensor intrin description */
2145struct TensorIntrinDescInfo {
2146 /*! \brief The block of the description function, which is the (unique) direct child of the root
2147 * block.
2148 */
2149 const BlockRealizeNode* desc_block = nullptr;
2150 /*! \brief The loops of the description function, in the order from outer loops to inner ones. */
2151 std::vector<const tir::ForNode*> desc_loops;
2152 /*! \brief The loop variables. */
2153 std::unordered_set<const tir::VarNode*> desc_loop_vars;
2154};

2156/*!
2157 * \brief Extract auxilary information from the tensor intrin description.
2158 * \param analyze The arithmetic analyzer
2159 * \param desc_func The description PrimFunc
2160 * \return The auxilary information
2161 */
2162TensorIntrinDescInfo ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(arith::Analyzer* analyzer,
2163 const PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2164 TensorIntrinDescInfo info;
2165 const auto* desc_scope_realize = desc_func->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>();
2166 ICHECK(desc_scope_realize);
2167 {
2168 auto f_visit = [&](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
2169 // Extract the block
2170 if (const auto* block = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
2171 info.desc_block = block;
2172 return false;
2173 }
2174 // Extract the loops
2175 if (const auto* loop = obj.as<ForNode>()) {
2176 info.desc_loops.push_back(loop);
2177 info.desc_loop_vars.insert(loop->loop_var.get());
2178 if (!analyzer->CanProve(loop->min == 0)) {
2179 return false;
2180 }
2181 }
2182 return true;
2183 };
2184 tir::PostOrderVisit(desc_scope_realize->block->body, f_visit);
2185 std::reverse(info.desc_loops.begin(), info.desc_loops.end());
2186 ICHECK(info.desc_block);
2187 }
2188 return info;
2189}
2190
2191Optional<TensorizeInfo> GetTensorizeLoopMapping(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
2192 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2193 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2194 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2195 const tir::BlockRealize& block = tir::GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref);
2196 // Step 1. Analyze desc_func, extract its block, loops and loop vars
2197 TensorIntrinDescInfo desc_info = ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(&analyzer, desc_func);
2198 // Step 2. Collect loops from block_sref
2199 const tir::StmtSRef& scope_sref = GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, false);
2200 TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
2201 std::vector<const tir::ForNode*> block_loops;
2202 std::unordered_set<const tir::VarNode*> block_loop_vars;
2203 {
2204 for (const tir::StmtSRefNode* loop_sref = block_sref->parent;; loop_sref = loop_sref->parent) {
2205 const auto* loop = loop_sref->StmtAs<tir::ForNode>();
2206 if (loop == nullptr || loop->body->IsInstance<tir::SeqStmtNode>()) {
2207 break;
2208 }
2209 block_loops.push_back(loop);
2210 block_loop_vars.insert(loop->loop_var.get());
2211 if (!analyzer.CanProve(loop->min == 0)) {
2212 return NullOpt;
2213 }
2214 }
2215 std::reverse(block_loops.begin(), block_loops.end());
2216 }
2217 // Step 3. Map from block loops to desc block loops
2218 const std::vector<const ForNode*>& desc_loops = desc_info.desc_loops;
2219 const std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>& desc_loop_vars = desc_info.desc_loop_vars;
2220 const BlockRealizeNode* desc_block = desc_info.desc_block;
2221 ObjectPtr<TensorizeInfoNode> ret = make_object<TensorizeInfoNode>();
2222 const int n_block_vars = block->iter_values.size();
2223 const int n_desc_vars = desc_block->iter_values.size();
2224 const int offset = n_block_vars - n_desc_vars;
2225
2226 if (offset < 0) {
2227 return NullOpt;
2228 }
2229
2230 const std::vector<IterVarType> iter_types_block = GetBlockVarTypes(block_sref);
2231 const std::vector<IterVarType> iter_types_desc = GetBlockVarTypes(desc_block->block.get());
2232
2233 ICHECK(desc_loops.size() == static_cast<size_t>(n_desc_vars));
2234 ICHECK(block_loops.size() == iter_types_block.size());
2235
2236 // We assume that the orders of iter_vars in the target and the desc block are consistent.
2237 // Based on that assumption, the following logic supports arbitrary permutations of a loop order,
2238 // such as
2239
2240 // for k:
2241 // for i:
2242 // for j:
2243 // C[i, j] += A[i, k] * B[k, j]
2244
2245 // or
2246
2247 // for i:
2248 // for j:
2249 // for k:
2250 // C[i, j] += A[i, k] * B[k, j]
2251
2252 int next_block_ind = block_loops.size() - 1;
2253 for (int i_desc = n_desc_vars - 1; i_desc >= 0; --i_desc) {
2254 // Step 3.1. Find the corresponding loop of the i_desc-th block var of desc
2255 const PrimExpr& desc_bind = desc_block->iter_values[i_desc];
2256 const tir::ForNode* desc_loop = nullptr;
2257 IterVarType iter_type_desc = iter_types_desc[i_desc];
2258 for (int i = 0, n = desc_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2259 // Check if desc_bind = loops[i]->loop_var + stuff-irrelevant-of-loop-vars
2260 PrimExpr residual = analyzer.Simplify(desc_bind - desc_loops[i]->loop_var);
2261 if (!UsesVar(residual,
2262 [&desc_loop_vars](const VarNode* var) { return desc_loop_vars.count(var); })) {
2263 desc_loop = desc_loops[i];
2264 iter_type_desc = iter_types_desc[i];
2265 break;
2266 }
2267 }
2268 if (desc_loop == nullptr || desc_loop->extent.as<IntImmNode>() == nullptr) {
2269 return NullOpt;
2270 }
2271
2272 const IntImmNode* int_desc_extent = desc_loop->extent.as<IntImmNode>();
2273
2274 // Step 3.2. Find the corresponding iter_value of the target block with a matching iterator type
2275 PrimExpr block_bind;
2276 for (int i = next_block_ind; i >= 0; --i) {
2277 if (iter_types_block[i] == iter_type_desc) {
2278 next_block_ind = i - 1;
2279 block_bind = block->iter_values[i];
2280 break;
2281 }
2282 }
2283
2284 if (!block_bind.defined()) return NullOpt;
2285
2286 // Step 3.3. Find the corresponding loop of the target block
2287 for (int i = 0, n = block_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2288 // Check if block_bind = block_loops[i]->loop_var + stuff-irrelevant-of-loop-vars
2289 const tir::ForNode* block_loop = block_loops[i];
2290 const tir::StmtSRef& block_loop_sref = self->stmt2ref[block_loop];
2291 // Skip i-th loop if it has already been mapped
2292 if (ret->loop_map.find(block_loop_sref) != ret->loop_map.end()) continue;
2293
2294 PrimExpr residual = analyzer.Simplify(block_bind - block_loops[i]->loop_var);
2295 if (UsesVar(residual,
2296 [&block_loop_vars](const VarNode* var) { return block_loop_vars.count(var); }))
2297 continue;
2298
2299 const IntImmNode* int_block_extent = block_loops[i]->extent.as<IntImmNode>();
2300
2301 // Check divisibility
2302 if (!int_block_extent || int_block_extent->value % int_desc_extent->value != 0) {
2303 return NullOpt;
2304 }
2305
2306 ret->loop_map.Set(block_loop_sref, GetRef<tir::For>(desc_loop));
2307 break;
2308 }
2309 }
2310
2311 for (int i = 0, n = desc_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2312 ret->desc_loop_indexer.Set(GetRef<tir::For>(desc_loops[i]), Integer(i));
2313 }
2314 return TensorizeInfo(ret);
2315}
