2323/******** Auto Tensorization ********/
2324
2325/*! \brief IndexMap proposer for layout transformation in auto tensorization. */
2326class AutoTensorizeMappingProposer {
2327 public:
2328 static Array<IndexMap> ProposeMappings(const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor,
2329 arith::Analyzer* analyzer) {
2330 AutoTensorizeMappingProposer proposer(extractor, analyzer);
2331 proposer.CollectFeasibleSet();
2332 return proposer.ProposeAllFuseMapping();
2333 }
2334
2335 private:
2336 explicit AutoTensorizeMappingProposer(const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor,
2337 arith::Analyzer* analyzer)
2338 : extractor_(extractor), analyzer_(analyzer) {}
2339
2340 using VarSet = std::unordered_set<Var, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual>;
2341
2342 void CollectFeasibleSet() {
2343 // Collect the set of potential iter var mapping between the workload and the tensor intrin.
2344 // We analyze the appearance of each variable in the buffer indices of each buffer on LHS and
2345 // RHS. The appearance of a variable in the buffer indices is encoded as bit-masks (BufferMask).
2346 // Variables on the LHS and the RHS with the same bit-mask and the same iter type are potential
2347 // mappings.
2348 //
2349 // For example, consider the conv2d case. We will try to match the workload
2350 // conv2d[n, h, w, c] = sum_{rh, rw, rc} X[n, h + rh, w + rw, c + rc] * W[rh, rw, rc, c]
2351 // against a matmul tensor intrin
2352 // C[m, n] = sum_{k} A[m, k] * B[k, n]
2353 // First we extract the correspondence of the buffers: conv2d <=> C, A <=> X, B <=> W.
2354 // Then for each variable, we extract the buffers where it is used for indexing.
2355 // Take the variable m on the RHS as an example. m is used to index buffer A and C. On the LHS,
2356 // we will find the variables used to index only the exact corresponding buffers conv2d and X
2357 // (the variable is not allowed to index other buffers). In this case, n, h, w is used to index
2358 // both buffer conv2d and W, and not in other buffers. Therefore, {n, h, w} <=> m is a potential
2359 // mapping.
2360
2361 // Note: the mapping is not unique when multiple variables on RHS has the same bit-mask.
2362 // This is currently not supported.
2363
2364 using BufferMask = std::vector<bool>;
2365
2366 // Step 1: Assign an index to each buffer in LHS and RHS
2367 std::unordered_map<Buffer, int, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectEqual> rhs_buffer_index;
2368 std::unordered_map<Buffer, int, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectEqual> lhs_buffer_index;
2369 {
2370 int i = 0;
2371 for (const auto& kv : extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_) {
2372 const Buffer& rhs_buffer = kv.first;
2373 const Buffer& lhs_buffer = kv.second;
2374 rhs_buffer_index[rhs_buffer] = i;
2375 lhs_buffer_index[lhs_buffer] = i;
2376 ++i;
2377 }
2378 }
2379
2380 // Step 2: Compute the buffer mask
2381 ICHECK_EQ(rhs_buffer_index.size(), lhs_buffer_index.size());
2382 int num_buffers = rhs_buffer_index.size();
2383 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::vector<bool>> rhs_buffer_masks, lhs_buffer_masks;
2384 // helper function to initialize or update the buffer mask
2385 auto update_mask = [&](const VarNode* var,
2386 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::vector<bool>>* masks, int i) {
2387 if (!masks->count(var)) {
2388 (*masks)[var].resize(num_buffers);
2389 }
2390 (*masks)[var][i] = true;
2391 };
2392
2393 for (const auto& it : extractor_->rhs_buffer_indices_map_) {
2394 const Buffer& rhs_buffer = it.first;
2395 for (const PrimExpr& rhs_index : it.second) {
2396 if (const VarNode* var_node = rhs_index.as<VarNode>()) {
2397 update_mask(var_node, &rhs_buffer_masks, rhs_buffer_index.at(rhs_buffer));
2398 } else {
2399 LOG(FATAL) << "ValueError: Buffer index " << rhs_index
2400 << " other that variables in tensor intrinsics is not supported.";
2401 }
2402 }
2403
2404 auto lhs_buffer_it = extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_.find(rhs_buffer);
2405 ICHECK(lhs_buffer_it != extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_.end());
2406 const Buffer& lhs_buffer = lhs_buffer_it->second;
2407 for (const PrimExpr& index : extractor_->lhs_buffer_indices_map_.at(lhs_buffer)) {
2408 PreOrderVisit(index, [&](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
2409 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
2410 update_mask(var, &lhs_buffer_masks, lhs_buffer_index.at(lhs_buffer));
2411 }
2412 return true;
2413 });
2414 }
2415 }
2416
2417 // Step 3: Find variables on LHS and RHS with the same buffer mask. Ensure LHS and RHS vars
2418 // have the same iter type.
2419 std::unordered_map<BufferMask, VarSet> mask_to_rhs_vars;
2420 for (const auto& kv : rhs_buffer_masks) {
2421 const VarNode* rhs_var = kv.first;
2422 const BufferMask& mask = kv.second;
2423 mask_to_rhs_vars[mask].insert(GetRef<Var>(rhs_var));
2424 }
2425 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType> rhs_var_iter_type;
2426 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
2427 rhs_var_iter_type.emplace(iter->var.get(), iter->iter_type);
2428 }
2429 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->lhs_iters_) {
2430 auto& potential_mappings = lhs_feasible_vars_[iter->var];
2431 VarSet rhs_candidates = mask_to_rhs_vars[lhs_buffer_masks[iter->var.get()]];
2432 std::copy_if(
2433 rhs_candidates.begin(), rhs_candidates.end(),
2434 std::inserter(potential_mappings, potential_mappings.begin()),
2435 [&](const Var& var) { return rhs_var_iter_type.at(var.get()) == iter->iter_type; });
2436 }
2437 }
2438
2439 Array<IndexMap> ProposeAllFuseMapping() {
2440 // Now we have calcuated potential mapping for each iter var on LHS. For iters on LHS mapped to
2441 // the same iter on RHS, they will be fused in the original order in LHS block iters. We will
2442 // generate IndexMap to represent such fusion on LHS. For example, if n, h, w on LHS are mapped
2443 // to the same iter var on RHS, we will produce index map `lambda n, h, w: fuse(n, h, w)`, where
2444 // fuse(v0, .., vn) = ((v0 * v1_extent + v1) + ... ) * vn_extent + vn
2445
2446 // the parameters of the result index map, each parameter corresponds to a LHS iter
2447 Array<Var> index_map_src;
2448 // the outputs of the result index map
2449 Array<PrimExpr> index_map_tgt;
2450
2451 // Step 1: Collect extents of LHS iters and prepare the initial indices of the IndexMap
2452 Map<Var, PrimExpr> lhs_iter_extents;
2453 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->lhs_iters_) {
2454 lhs_iter_extents.Set(iter->var, iter->dom->extent);
2455 index_map_src.push_back(iter->var.copy_with_suffix(""));
2456 }
2457
2458 // Step 2: Each iter on RHS has a group of corresponding iters on LHS. Initialize the fusion
2459 // result for each group of iters on LHS.
2460 Map<Var, PrimExpr> fused_lhs_iters;
2461 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
2462 fused_lhs_iters.Set(iter->var, 0);
2463 }
2464
2465 // Step 3: Fuse LHS iters mapped to the same RHS iter
2466 std::unordered_set<Var, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> used_rhs_vars;
2467 for (size_t i = 0; i < extractor_->lhs_iters_.size(); ++i) {
2468 const Var& lhs_iter_var = extractor_->lhs_iters_[i]->var;
2469 const VarSet& rhs_candidates = lhs_feasible_vars_[lhs_iter_var];
2470 if (rhs_candidates.empty()) {
2471 // put unmapped iters at the beginning
2472 index_map_tgt.push_back(index_map_src[i]);
2473 } else if (rhs_candidates.size() == 1) {
2474 Var rhs_var = *rhs_candidates.begin();
2475 PrimExpr fused_lhs = fused_lhs_iters.at(rhs_var);
2476 PrimExpr updated_fused_lhs =
2477 fused_lhs * lhs_iter_extents.at(lhs_iter_var) + index_map_src[i];
2478 fused_lhs_iters.Set(rhs_var, updated_fused_lhs);
2479 used_rhs_vars.insert(rhs_var);
2480 } else {
2481 // non-unique mapping is not supported
2482 return {};
2483 }
2484 }
2485 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
2486 if (!used_rhs_vars.count(iter->var)) {
2487 return {};
2488 }
2489 index_map_tgt.push_back(analyzer_->Simplify(fused_lhs_iters[iter->var]));
2490 }
2491 // At most one mapping is supported.
2492 return {IndexMap(index_map_src, index_map_tgt)};
2493 }
2494
2495 private:
2496 // The extractor that has extracted information for auto tensorization from the workload and the
2497 // tensor intrin.
2498 const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor_;
2499 // The arithmetic analyzer.
2500 arith::Analyzer* analyzer_;
2501 /*! \brief Potential mappings on RHS for each variable on LHS */
2502 std::unordered_map<Var, VarSet, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> lhs_feasible_vars_;
2503};
2504
2505bool CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(const ScheduleState& state, const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2506 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func,
2507 AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor) {
2508 // Step 1. Analyze desc_func, extract its block, loops and loop vars
2509 // Step 2. Check if `desc_block` matches `block`
2510 // Ignore the scope of buffers when comparing, since we can do cache_read/write
2511 const BlockRealize& block = tir::GetBlockRealize(state, block_sref);
2512 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2513 auto desc_info = tir::ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(&analyzer, desc_func);
2514
2515 return extractor->VisitStmt(block->block, desc_info.desc_block->block);
2516}
2517
2518bool CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(const tir::Schedule& sch, const tir::BlockRV& block_rv,
2519 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2520 AutoTensorizeComparator extractor(sch->state()->mod);
2521 return CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(sch->state(), sch->GetSRef(block_rv), desc_func, &extractor);
2522}
2523
2524Optional<AutoTensorizeMappingInfo> GetAutoTensorizeMappingInfo(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
2525 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2526 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2527 AutoTensorizeComparator extractor(self->mod);
2528 if (!CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(self, block_sref, desc_func, &extractor)) {
2529 return NullOpt;
2530 }
2531 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2532 Array<IndexMap> mappings = AutoTensorizeMappingProposer::ProposeMappings(&extractor, &analyzer);
2533 if (mappings.empty()) {
2534 return NullOpt;
2535 }
2536 ObjectPtr<AutoTensorizeMappingInfoNode> ret = make_object<AutoTensorizeMappingInfoNode>();
2537 ret->mappings = std::move(mappings);
2538 ret->lhs_buffer_map = std::move(extractor.lhs_buffer_map_);
2539 ret->rhs_buffer_indices = std::move(extractor.rhs_buffer_indices_map_);
2540 ret->lhs_iters = std::move(extractor.lhs_iters_);
2541 ret->rhs_iters = std::move(extractor.rhs_iters_);
2542 return AutoTensorizeMappingInfo(ret);
2543}
